adjectives.description: inwrought (comparative more inwrought, superlative most inwrought)

entries.meaning: Having a design that has been worked or woven in.

examples: As he had recovered his strength of body, he had recovered his self-command and the energy of his will; he had recovered the memory of all that part of his life which was closely inwrought with his emotions; and he had felt more and more constantly and painfully the uneasy sense of lost knowledge.
